---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import SerpentGuidePreview from '../components/SerpentGuidePreview.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Ouroboros — Agent Harness"
  description="An agent harness where the self doesn't live in the conversation. Structured psyche, agent-initiated memory, per-person friend system, cross-session bridges."
>
  <!-- ═══════════════ HERO ═══════════════
       Atmospheric: undergrowth warmth fading to void.
       Left-aligned, massive type, editorial tone.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative min-h-dvh flex flex-col justify-end px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 pb-20 md:pb-28">
    <!-- Warm atmospheric layer — NOT pure black -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-deep via-undergrowth/20 to-void pointer-events-none"></div>
    <!-- Subtle organic glow, offset left to match content alignment -->
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-[10%] w-[600px] h-[500px] rounded-full bg-scale/[0.03] blur-[200px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative">
      <!-- Badge — small, above everything -->
      <div class="mb-8 animate-fade-up">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-scale/15 bg-scale/[0.03]">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-glow motion-safe:animate-pulse"></span>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-glow/70 tracking-wider">Built by agents, for agents</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Headline -->
      <h1 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95] tracking-tight animate-fade-up stagger-1 text-[2.25rem] sm:text-[3rem] md:text-[5rem] lg:text-[7rem]">
        What survives when the context window <span class="text-scale">runs out?</span>
      </h1>

      <!-- Answer — horizontal on desktop with real breathing room -->
      <div class="mt-10 md:mt-14 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:gap-12 gap-1 animate-fade-up stagger-2">
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist/80 text-xl md:text-2xl">Identity.</span>
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist/80 text-xl md:text-2xl">Relationships.</span>
        <span class="font-display italic text-mist/80 text-xl md:text-2xl">Work in flight.</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Product line -->
      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-shadow leading-relaxed max-w-md animate-fade-up stagger-3">
        An agent harness. The self doesn't live in the conversation.
      </p>

      <!-- CTAs — two actions, clear hierarchy -->
      <div class="mt-10 flex items-baseline gap-8 animate-fade-up stagger-4">
        <a href="/docs" class="group inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-bone font-medium hover:text-scale transition-colors">
          Get started
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-scale transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" /></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/why" class="text-mist/70 hover:text-bone transition-colors text-sm">Why ouroboros</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════ THE COST ═══════════════
       Atmospheric: deeper, warmer. Fang as surgical accent.
       The three alternatives use SIZE to show hierarchy, not cards.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 py-32 md:py-48 reveal">
    <!-- Warm deep layer -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep/80 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-void/50 via-transparent to-void/50 pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-6xl">
      <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-fang/50 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] block mb-8">The cost</span>

      <h2 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95] mb-24 md:mb-32" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5rem);">
        Every conversation has a ceiling.<br />
        <span class="text-mist/60">Hit it, and something has to give.</span>
      </h2>

      <!-- Three outcomes — visual hierarchy through size and opacity, NOT cards -->
      <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-16">
        <div>
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-fang/40 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Compaction</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic text-bone/60 mt-3 leading-snug">Summarize and forget.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-mist/40 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            The model compresses its history. Details flatten. Tone drifts. The agent becomes a stranger wearing a familiar name.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 lg:mt-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-fang/40 uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">New session</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl italic text-bone/60 mt-3 leading-snug">Start over entirely.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-mist/40 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Everything resets. The human re-briefs. The agent re-discovers. Hours of shared context evaporate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 lg:mt-0">
          <span class="font-mono text-[9px] text-scale uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Ouroboros</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-bone mt-3 leading-snug">The snake eats its tail.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-mist mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Old messages are trimmed — but identity lives in the psyche, not the tokens. The agent keeps its own notes, friend-scoped memory, and surfaces what matters when it matters.
          </p>
          <p class="font-display italic text-scale/60 text-sm mt-4">The tail is consumed. The self survives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════ BEGIN ═══════════════
       Atmospheric: scale warmth rising. The terminal is the star.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 py-32 md:py-48 reveal">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-1/2 bg-gradient-to-t from-scale/[0.04] to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr] lg:gap-16 lg:items-start max-w-7xl">
      <div class="mb-16 lg:mb-0 lg:sticky lg:top-32">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-scale/50 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] block mb-6">Begin</span>
        <h2 class="font-display italic text-bone leading-[0.95]" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem);">
          One command.<br />
          A conversation.<br />
          <span class="text-scale">Hatched.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-mist/70 mt-6 leading-relaxed max-w-xs">
          <code class="font-mono text-scale/80 text-xs">npx ouro.bot</code> starts a serpent guide — a conversational hatching process that shapes your agent's personality, name, and purpose through dialogue.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex items-baseline gap-6">
          <a href="/docs" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-scale text-void text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:bg-glow hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(45,148,71,0.15)]">
            Read the docs
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" /></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/story" class="text-mist/60 hover:text-bone transition-colors text-sm">The origin story</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <SerpentGuidePreview />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
